The paper proposes a novel hierarchical agent architecture for multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a popular topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The architecture involves factorising the value function and policy into latent representations, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and social dilemmas, which are common challenges in multi-agent reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a meta-policy, which is a technique commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). Overall, the paper covers a range of topics that are relevant to several sub-categories of arXiv CS, with cs.AI and cs.LG being the most likely categories.
